            <p><strong>What are some of the benefits of the Program for startups?</strong><br></p>
                  <ul><li>Tailored development curriculum: hands-on coaching through GVS’ Transmedia Project Pipeline to polish and package franchise portfolios (including developing the investor presentation and pitch practice)</li>
                  <li>Mentors: one on one advising from experienced professionals</li>
                  <li>Synergy and momentum: the Cohort dynamic and the growing industry
                    ecosystem around the Accelerator</li>
                  <li>Networking: selected startups will benefit from introductions and industry
                    relationships with our standout advisory committee and consultants</li>
                  <li>Access: top quality legal counsel, marketing professionals</li>
                  <li>Accelerator Showcase upon graduation</li>
                  <li>Creative Community Events & Speaker Series: gatherings, screenings,
                    creative collaborations, topical seminars, peer work-shopping and more</li></ul>

                  <p><strong>What would a typical week look like for a startup going through the Accelerator?</strong><br>
                    Each startup company will be on it’s own curriculum respective of its specific needs. Companies will work closely with their coach to set benchmarks and review development progress on a weekly basis in collaboration with their mentor(s). Entire cohort workshops and seminars will be organized at strategic junctures of the cycle and at the availability of key speakers and industry professionals.</p>

                  <p><strong>Could my company use the seed funding however we like?</strong><br>
                    Candidates will work together with Accelerator coaches to determine the most effective use of startup funds. A proposed budget is then submitted in cooperation with the Executive Board for final consideration and funding.</p>
                  <p><strong>Do I have to commit to the whole 6-month intensive period?</strong><br>
                    Each company will have its own needs and work at its own pace. If you are selected and receive seed funding, you are expected to complete the acceleration process at the advice and direction of your coach and mentors.</p>
                  <p><strong>Do I have to live in Kona during the intensive period?</strong><br>
                    No, you do not. Team members will, however, be required to attend certain workshops, seminars and events at the facility.</p>
                  <p><strong>What happens after the 6-month intensive period?</strong><br>
                    At the end of the six-month intensive program, each company will have a polished and packaged transmedia franchise plan, including a business plan and investor presentation for at least three different expressions of their IP constituting multiple revenue streams. This portion of the program will end with an investor Showcase Day attended by potential follow-on funders including those in the networks of Accelerator advisors, mentors and consultants. Companies will then be poised to rapidly raise follow-on funding over the next six-month period of supported pitching and fundraising.</p>
                  <p><strong>Do I have to raise follow-on funding immediately after my company’s acceleration period?</strong><br>
                    Yes - unless company founders, Accelerator coaches and mentors agree that the company needs further development.</p>
                  <p><strong>Does the Program fund non-profits?</strong><br>
                    The Program is a for profit venture and as such, the GTA Development Fund will not select non-profit companies for acceleration. Investors are looking to recoup and receive competitive returns on their capital.</p>
                  <p><strong>What sort of partnership will I be entering into with the GTA Development Fund? What sort of control am I giving to the Fund by granting it equity in my company?</strong><br>
                    The GTA Development Fund will be a minority interest owner at 10% equity stake. Essentially, the Fund doesn’t want any special or controlling interests in your company or uncommon investor rights, nor does the Fund need a board seat. Just looking for a great return on a great investment!</p>

